"n.教义，信条 【英】 n. 教义，信条(any doctrine or rule widely or ardently maintained) 【记】 来自《圣经·新约》中 的福音书(Gospel),可 能来自god+spell→上 帝的话→信条 n. 绝对真理(毫无疑问是真实的东西, 思想或原则); 【记】源于《圣经?新约》中的福音书(Gospel), 是基督教《启示录》的中心内容. 福音书是新约圣经的前四本书之一, 记载了耶稣的生平、死亡、复活和他的教导go = god, spel = spell拼写－上帝的拼写－绝对真理 【记】god 神 + spell 拼写，咒语→神的话，神的音讯→福音 gospel (n.)  Old English godspel ""gospel, glad tidings announced by Jesus; one of the four gospels,"" from god ""good"" (see good) + spel ""story, message"" (see spell (n.1)); translation of Latin bona adnuntiatio, itself a translation of Greek euangelion ""reward for bringing good news."" The first element of the Old English word had a long ""o,"" but it shifted under mistaken association with God. The word passed early from English to continental Germanic languages in forms that clearly indicate the first element had shifted to ""God,"" such as Old Saxon godspell, Old High German gotspell, Old Norse goðspiall. Used of anything as true as the Gospel from mid-13c. Gospel-gossip was Addison's word (""Spectator,"" 1711) for ""one who is always talking of sermons, texts, etc."""
